<p><strong>Saving Throws</strong> Int +5, Wis +6, Cha +7</p>

<p><strong>Skills</strong> Deception +7, Insight +6</p>

<p><strong>Damage Resistances</strong> cold, bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from nonmagical weapons that aren’t silvered</p>

<p><strong>Damage Immunities</strong> fire, poison</p>

<p><strong>Condition Immunities</strong> poisoned</p>

<p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 120 ft.</p>

<p><strong>Languages</strong> Infernal, telepathy 120 ft.</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 12 (8,400 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Devil’s Sight.</em></strong> Magical darkness doesn’t impede the devil’s darkvision.</p>

<p><strong><em>Magic Resistance.</em></strong> The devil has advantage on saving throws against spells and other magical effects.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Multiattack.</em></strong> The devil makes three attacks: two with its claws and one with its sting.</p>

<p><strong><em>Claw.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +8 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. Hit: 8 (1d8 + 4) slashing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Sting.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +8 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. Hit: 13 (2d8 + 4) piercing damage plus 17 (5d6) poison damage, and the target must succeed on a DC 14 Constitution saving throw or become poisoned for 1 minute. The target can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success .</p>

